Release critical
----------------
* Cleanup Exscript.protocols.Exceptions.
* Can Exscript.protocols.Transport have a Python stream interface?
* Get rid of the model and vendor detection.
* Add API docs for Exscript.protocols.Exceptions.
* Move SpiffWorkQueue to Exscript.workqueue.
* Use this automated version numbering scheme:
  http://michaelandlaura.org.uk/~michael/blog/index.php?id=379
* Add util.decorator.marshal(func, *data, **kwargs).
* In util.start, use marshallers to bind args to the function,
  and use the args und kwargs to init the queue instead.

Other
-----
* Add a recursive test target.
* Port to Python's OptionParser.
* Get rid of FooLib.OptionParser.
* Move utilTest to a new utils subdir (similar to protocols).
* Move Exscript.protocols.otp to Exscript.util.
* Move Exscript.FooLib to Exscript.util.
* Add more tests.
* "make dist" should pull dependencies.
